DURBAN - Five suspected robbers were killed following a cash in transit heist in Springfield on Monday. Paramedics rushed two civilians to hospital who were caught in the cross fire between the gang and the police. The men allegedly robbed a cash van that had just dropped off money at Makro. Police responded to the robbery. According to police sources when the men saw the police, they began shooting and police fired back.  A man was killed in Springfield. A high speed chase ensued through the streets around Springfield with police closing in on the gang in the nearby suburb of Parlock. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. VIDEO: Police K9 Units search the bushes for two robbers who escaped In Parlock, police and the gang exchanged gunfire. Four more men were shot dead. Police launched a a manhunt for two robbers who escaped. The vehicle used by the men had also been recovered. Daily News